From Wiktionary, the free dictionary

German

[edit]

Alternative forms

[edit]
  • Müntze (obsolete spelling)

Etymology 1

[edit]

From Middle High German münze, from Old High German muniz, munizza, from Proto-West Germanic *munit.

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): [ˈmʏnt͡sə]
  • Audio:(file)
  • Hyphenation: Mün‧ze

Noun

[edit]

Münze f (genitive Münze, plural Münzen)

  1. money, in its senses as
    1. a coin, a metallic piece of currency
    2. coinage, a system of currency
  2. mint (building or institution where coins are produced)
Declension
[edit]

Synonyms
[edit]
  • (coin): Kleingeld, Geldstück
  • (mint): Münzanstalt, Münzprägeanstalt, Münzstätte
